feat(rate-limit.ts): implement general API rate limiter with 100 requests per hour
Introduce a new function `apiRateLimit` to enforce a rate limit of 100 requests per hour per IP address. This helps prevent abuse and ensures fair usage of the API. The function tracks requests by IP and resets the count every hour. If the limit is exceeded, it returns a 429 status with an error message.
refactor(middleware.ts): replace RateLimiter with specific rate limit functions
